parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power sliding doors can cause safety issues, especially for children, as they may not be able to exit the vehicle in an emergency.
symptoms: The power sliding doors fail to open or close
or become stuck
making it difficult or impossible to enter or exit the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of safety issues, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of critical systems such as airbags and lights.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
lights fail to function
or the electrical system malfunctions
causing a range of safety issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
indicating a fault in the system
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lighting system can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights or interior lights fail to function
or malfunction
causing reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral or reverse while in motion
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle rolls away while in park
and the transmission makes a loud noise or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical components can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the gauges on the dashboard malfunction
the power windows operate without the key
and the vehicle's headlights remain on even when turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank/Vapor Liquid Separator Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank/vapor liquid separator valve can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after refueling
often when pulling into traffic or stopping at an intersection; the engine hesitates
sputters
or dies; the vehicle may restart after a few attempts; the problem is more frequent when the fuel tank is filled to capacity.
